{"title": "Shakespeare at the Globe, 1599-1609", "description": "One of the most important pieces of Shakespearian scholarship to appear in several years, this brilliant work offers new perspectives on the controversial subject of Shakespearean production at the Globe. The author examines the Globe's repertory system, dramaturgy, stage, acting, and staging. Dr. Beckerman is Chairman of the Department of Drama and Speech at Hofstra College, where he directs the annual Shakespearean Festival on a detailed replica of the Globe Theatre stage. His acute observation and sound logic, as well as his practical experience as a producer, make this volume a useful and comprehensive account of the productions at the globe. - Summary by H. Lawrence Hoffman", "duration": 35933, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17041", "name": "Bernard Beckerman"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/shakespeareattheglobe_1599-1609_2212_librivox/shakespeareglobe_2212.jpg", "copyright_year": "1962", "genres": ["Performing Arts"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "James R. Hedrick"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "James R. Hedrick"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Jenn Broda"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shakespeareattheglobe_1599-1609_2212_librivox/shakespeareglobe_00_beckerman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1341}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter One - The Repertory Part 1", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shakespeareattheglobe_1599-1609_2212_librivox/shakespeareglobe_01_beckerman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1857}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter One - The Repertory Part 2", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shakespeareattheglobe_1599-1609_2212_librivox/shakespeareglobe_02_beckerman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1995}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter Two - The Dramaturgy", "rea